The deputy president of the Senate, Senator Ovie Omo-Agege, has expressed deep shock and grief over the death of the daughter of the former governor of Sokoto State and Senator representing Sokoto North, Aliyu Magatakarda Wamakko. Wammako, who chairs the Senate Committee on Defence, lost his daughter, Sadiya at the Usmanu Danfodiyo University Teaching Hospital, Sokoto State, following complications associated with childbirth. A statement by the special adviser, media and publicity to the deputy Senate president, Yomi Odunuga, and made available to LEADERSHIP Weekend, said Omo-Agege expressed sadness over the development and prayed for God Almighty to comfort his grieving colleague and grant him fortitude.